article.headline: Tennessee Tech 82, SE Missouri State 81 (OT)
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Willie Jenkins had 34 points, including a 3-pointer with 17 seconds left, to lead Tennessee Tech to an 82-81 overtime win over Southeast Missouri State on Thursday night. After Jenkins 3-pointer, Southeast Missouri's Reggie Golson missed a 3-pointer at the buzzer, giving the Golden Eagles (10-6, 5-0 Ohio Valley Conference) the win. The Indians (6-10, 1-4) led through most the game, taking a 33-26 halftime lead. But Tennessee Tech shot 60 percent (18-of-30) from the field in the second half, making a comeback late into the game to take it into overtime. The game was tied 70-70 after regulation. Jenkins also had 10 rebounds for the Golden Eagles, who outrebounded Southeast Missouri 40-25. Derek Strebling had 23 points for Tennessee Tech. Dainmon Gonner led four Southeast Missouri players in double digits with 19 points. Reggie Golson had 17 points and nine rebounds, Derek Winans had 13 points, and Terrick Willoughby added 10 points. The Golden Eagles shot 51 percent (30-of-59) overall from the field, while the Indians shot 43 percent (25-of-58).
